eNCA speaks to Xolani Fihla who is the spokesperson for the Johannesburg Metropolitan Police Department. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Johannesburg hasn't had any working speed cameras for more than a year. All speed prosecutions in the city have been halted since 31 May 2021. EXCLUSIVE | WATCH | Joburg Roads Agency corruption scandal The Johannesburg Metropolitan Police Department says the tender to repair or supply speed cameras in the city closed earlier this month, and they're hoping to have the issue resolved by the end of June. But in the meantime, the city has lost millions in revenue and will continue to do so.